https://leetcode.com/problems/delete-and-earn/description/

QUESTION:
Input: nums = [3,4,2]
Output: 6

Input: nums = [2,2,3,3,3,4]
Output: 9
SOLUTION:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TIME  COMPLEXITY:O(N)
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(N)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 1: create a dp array
Step 2: loop through adding up if the elements are same
for example: [2 2 3 3 3 4] the dp array will be [2 6 0] 
              0 2 0 3 6 0
Step 4: Create a skip and take element.
Step 5: if you skip(take max of skip or take)
        if you take then add prev skip value and the current dp[i] value
Step 6: parse through.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CODE:
class Solution {
    public int deleteAndEarn(int[] nums) {
        int []dp=new int[10001];
        for(int num:nums){
            dp[num]+=num;
        }
        int skip=0,take=0;
        for(int i=0;i<dp.length;i++){
            int c_skip=Math.max(skip,take);
            int c_take=skip+dp[i];
            skip=c_skip;
            take=c_take;
        }
        return Math.max(skip,take);
    }
}
